history.content: I've heard 61B over the summer can be a really good experience as well (not sure about 70), but honestly taking either of them should be fine; I would take 70 for the sole reason that 61B + 61A projects overlapping could be tricky at times, but it's up to you.

children.subject: Yes after some thought, I️ realized especially all 3 together were a horrible idea. Although, I️ do have confidence in the fact that I️ have all the work for CS61a finished and I’ve already reviewed the material for the first half of 70. I️ think I’m going to take CS61a, CS70, EE16a, and theater, than eventually choose between CS70 or EE16a. Thanks so much :-)

I’d recommend not taking any of the 61/70 concurrently tbh so I’d go with 16a. I know some ppl who take  some of these classes and breeze through but unless you know you are one of those people, there’s really just no point (since you are a freshman)

61b in summer so you can solely focus on it when you take it as it’s the most

important class you’ll take

70 after that

history.content:
Im a freshman who audited cs61a this semester and will have all the homeworks, labs, and projects done. I've done practice midterms and finals and I tend to score pretty well (70ish). I want to take advantage of this preparation and take another CS prerequisite with CS61A. My only other class is theater10, which is fun, and not time consuming at all. What class should I take with CS61A next semester? CS61B, CS70, or EE16A? I should note that I've started learning CS70 already b/c that was what I was originally going to take with CS61A. However, I was intrigued by next semester's cs61b professor as I hear he's amazing. Furthermore, all my friends will be taking cs61b and cs70 so I will have help with both. Oh, and I'm also going to take whatever class I end up dropping over this summer. For example, if next semester is 61a, cs70, and theater, ill take cs61b over the summer, and if it was 61a, 61b, and theater this semester, id take 70 over the summer.

Thank you!
history.subject: What class to take with CS61A (audited it)
